																		Author Post
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205739" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1554764640 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Apr 2019 23:04</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4213144">
									

<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Can I tell you something<br />
Got to tell you one thing<br />
If you expect the freedom<br />
That you say is yours<br />
Prove that you deserve it<br />
Help us to preserve it<br />
Or being free will just be<br />
Words and nothing more</em></p>
<p><span style="margin-left: 50%">Kansas &#8212; &quot;<a href="https://youtu.be/a-gIEZ7ID-U">Can I Tell You</a>&quot;</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Part 3 is here. Thanks to TyGently, tawny, and 9Volt for crit. Part 4 will be out on Friday, and will bring with it some good, clean, Nazi-punching action.</p>
<p>The first two tales of this 9-part series (nonology?) formed a sort of self-contained duology about how Florence came to the Foundation. Tales 3 and 4 will be forming their own duology, mostly about punching Nazis. 5, 6, and 7 will form a trilogy that will be released next week (assuming that I can get all the editing I need to do on them done in time), which will be mostly slice-of-life style stuff. 8 and 9 will close out the series with a duology about how Florence leaves the Foundation.</p>
<p>There's some more I wanted to put into this, but honestly, y'all probably don't care about the minute details of how Delta-3/Kappa-1 are organized.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;But&nbsp;in&nbsp;case&nbsp;you&nbsp;do&nbsp;care...</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-Here's&nbsp;some&nbsp;details</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>MTF Kappa-1 &quot;Sherman's March&quot; is a provisional task force that was formed to capture Florence.</li>
<li>After capturing Florence, Kappa-1 was dissolved and reorganized as MTF Delta-3 &quot;Solomon's Hand&quot;, under the aegis of the Special Asset Task Force Program.</li>
<li>While Julian Corwin is the nominal commander of Kappa-1 and Delta-3, field command of both task forces is held by Cody Westbrook. This is because Corwin is a badass old man who refuses to retire. Don't worry, the O5s eventually get him behind a desk, permanently.</li>
<li>While Delta-3 is organized around Florence and her abilities, it's not really <em>her</em> task force &#8212; she operates as a mostly independent unit, with Westbrook acting as a go-between for the rest of the task force. Delta-3's job is mostly in a support role &#8212; crowd control, perimeter security, etc&#8230; They're also there to contain Florence, if necessary, although she isn't supposed to know that part.</li>
<li>Florence is astonishingly, stupidly powerful, and the next tale will make that extremely clear if it wasn't already. She's also really, really, <em>really</em> imprecise. She is basically a magic sledgehammer, and her inability to do precision thaumaturgy is a much greater handicap than it might seem &#8212; anybody with an Everhart Resonator and a bit of time can pull out raw power, after all. We'll be exploring this later in the series, so don't worry if it seems like I'm just creating an X-man. Things are only gonna get worse for our heroine from here.
<ul>
<li>If you want, like, a direct power scale contrast, Florence is probably as or more powerful than Vincent Anderson, but he easily beats her when it comes to skill. They're both what I would consider high A tier thaumaturges. Robin Thorne, on the other hand, is probably down in low B tier, but they make up for it with cunning.</li>
<li>To give an even greater direct contrast, of all the magic stuff that Thorne does in <a href="/a-farewell-to-kings">A Farewell To Kings</a> and <a href="/moving-pictures">Moving Pictures</a>, the big fireball at the end is probably the only thing Florence could reliably do &#8212; but she could do it pretty much indefinitely, whereas in Moving Pictures, it basically took Thorne out of the picture.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Edit: Added an image for the Delta-3 patch logo, which I made myself. It's released under CC-BY-SA 3.0.</p>

